CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 16, 1957, pg. 3, reads: "Redevelopment Family - Richard Faye and his four youngsters peep through one of the many holes in bannisters of the stair rails through which toddlers could drop many feet below. He lived at 1104 Wylie Ave.; had to move when pipes were torn out for razing.  Says house he was sent to by Redevelopment Authority was worse than this."
TitMainTitle: Richard Faye and his three children, standing in apartment building behind wooden railing with broken spindles, 1015 Western Avenue, Northside
